# SuperHabits — Project Rules

## Project identity
SuperHabits is an offline-first React Native + Expo app with 5 modules:
todos, habits, pomodoro, workout, calories.
Stack: React Native 0.83, Expo 55, TypeScript 5.9, expo-router, SQLite
(expo-sqlite WAL mode), NativeWind 4, React Query 5, Vitest.
Target: Web (PWA), iOS, Android.
Status: Active MVP. No production deployment pipeline yet.
Schema version: 3. Next migration number: 4.

## Non-negotiable invariants — violating these causes silent data corruption

1. SOFT DELETE ONLY
   Never use DELETE FROM on main entity tables (todos, habits, habit_completions
   is the exception, workout_logs, calorie_entries, pomodoro_sessions).
   Always set deleted_at = datetime('now') and filter WHERE deleted_at IS NULL.
   Hard delete = data loss with no recovery path.

2. SYNC ENQUEUE ON EVERY WRITE
   Every INSERT/UPDATE on main entities must call syncEngine.enqueue(record)
   immediately after the DB operation.
   Exceptions (intentionally not synced): pomodoro_sessions, workout_logs,
   habit_completions.
   Missing enqueue = silent sync gap when cloud sync is enabled.

3. DB SINGLETON MUST INITIALIZE BEFORE ANY DATA ACCESS
   All data functions call await getDatabase() at the start.
   Never open a second SQLite connection. Never access db before init.
   Breaking the singleton breaks the entire app on cold start.

4. IDs VIA createId(prefix) ONLY
   Never use Math.random(), crypto.randomUUID(), or raw timestamps as IDs.
   Format: {prefix}_{timestamp}_{random8} — enforced in lib/id.ts.
   Prefix must match the entity: "todo", "habit", "cal", "wrk", "pom".

5. DATE KEYS VIA toDateKey() ONLY
   All YYYY-MM-DD date strings must come from toDateKey() in lib/time.ts.
   KNOWN BUG: toDateKey() currently uses UTC not local time. Do NOT fix
   this silently — it will corrupt historical records. Flag it explicitly
   if you touch date handling.

6. MIGRATIONS ARE APPEND-ONLY AND MONOTONICALLY INCREASING
   Never modify an existing migration. Always add a new file numbered N+1.
   Current schema version: 3. Next: 4.
   Migration logic runs in core/db/client.ts — add new case to the switch.
   schema.sql is a reference doc only — it is NOT executed at runtime.

7. UNIQUE(habit_id, date_key) on habit_completions
   Never INSERT a completion without checking for duplicates.
   The data layer uses INSERT OR REPLACE — do not change this pattern.

## File naming conventions
- Source files: camelCase (e.g. todoHelpers.ts)
- React components: PascalCase (e.g. TodoCard.tsx)
- Data layer: {feature}.data.ts (e.g. todos.data.ts)
- Domain/pure logic: {feature}.domain.ts (e.g. habits.domain.ts)
- Screens: {Feature}Screen.tsx (e.g. TodosScreen.tsx)
- Route wrappers: app/(tabs)/{feature}.tsx — thin, just renders the Screen

## Adding a new feature — required structure
features/{name}/
  {name}.data.ts      ← all SQLite CRUD, exports typed functions
  {name}.domain.ts    ← pure logic, no DB imports, fully testable
  {name}Screen.tsx    ← React Native UI, imports from .data and .domain

Route file: app/(tabs)/{name}.tsx → renders {Name}Screen
Tab entry: app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx → add tab icon + href

## Unused dependencies — do NOT add usage without discussion
The following are installed but intentionally unused:
- zustand (state management — may be used for future global state)
- @tanstack/react-query (no hooks used — QueryClient provided but dormant)
- date-fns (listed in package.json, not imported anywhere in source)
- expo-background-fetch, expo-task-manager (deferred background sync)
Do not wire these up without an explicit decision to do so.

## Testing requirements
- Every new *.domain.ts function must have a Vitest unit test
- Test files live in tests/ directory
- Run: npm test
- Current count: 6 tests passing
- No DB or component tests yet — do not block on this, but document gaps

## Current known bugs (do not silently fix — coordinate first)
- toDateKey() uses UTC not local time (lib/time.ts)
- Meal type hard-coded to "snack" in calories.data.ts
- nextPomodoroState() is dead code (pomodoro.domain.ts)
- Sync queue is in-memory only, never flushed
- schema.sql is out of date (reference only, not authoritative)
